Zedium — a community fork of Zed
================================

Zedium is an independent, community-maintained fork of the Zed editor
(https://github.com/zed-industries/zed).

Zedium is NOT affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Zed
Industries, Inc. "Zed" and the Zed logo are trademarks of Zed
Industries, Inc. and are not used by this project as source identifiers;
Zedium uses its own name and logo.

Copyright for the original Zed source code remains with Zed Industries,
Inc. and the respective contributors. Zedium's modifications are
copyright the Zedium contributors.

Licensing is unchanged from upstream: see LICENSE-GPL for the editor
(GPL-3.0-or-later) and LICENSE-APACHE for the components licensed under
Apache-2.0 (including GPUI and the extension API). All upstream license
files and copyright notices are preserved.

Zedium disables Zed's hosted-service integrations by default (telemetry,
crash reporting, and automatic updates from Zed Industries' servers).
Use of any Zed Industries hosted service from a Zedium build is subject
to Zed Industries' own terms of service.
